From 5b308d8c131d5d7624d47735289b0ead8ea35bd6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 19:39:23 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Segregation of Monitor
 Objects in Unified Driver Framework

With the Unified Driver framework, to support different monitor mode
variants quad ring model(mon1) for wcn family and dual ring model(mon2)
for qcn family and for better view of monitor object, segregating
monitor-related rings and objects from Data path object (DP) and
defining them in the monitor object (dp_mon).
Allocation and deallocation of the monitor object are done dynamically.

This patch (and the forthcoming patches) is intended to serve the
purpose of refactoring DP objects to DP monitor objects
for the Unified Driver framework.

Patch-dependency:
	0401-0013-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-enable-monitor-mode-for-WCN7.patch

Signed-off-by: Sushant Butta <sbutta@qti.qualcomm.com>
